In this lab, we practiced Java object-oriented programming concepts such as inheritance, constructors, method overriding and polymorphism. We created a base Person class and extended it into Student, Employee and Manager classes with additional fields and methods. We used super() to call parent constructors and override methods to change behavior in child classes. Finally, we used polymorphism by storing different objects in a Person array and calling the same method on each one. This lab showed how inheritance helps organize and reuse code efficiently.
